{"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","modules":[{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view#Define-the-view-basics","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Define-information-cards"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase#Discover-main-components","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase#Merge-components-in-a-richer-view","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase#Navigations-and-themeable-view-a-step-further","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Components-showcases"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-4-going-further#More-resources","kind":"task"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-4-going-further"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Go-further-with-more-ressources"}],"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/$volume","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies"},"sections":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework for Apple platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"kind":"hero","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.3","title":"Swift Package integration","projectFiles":"OUDS-Onboarding-Tutorial.zip"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","stepsSection":[{"type":"step","code":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using Xcode, in your ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"project package dependencies","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", add a new ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ouds-ios","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" dependency.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can then choose the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency rule","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" you want.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and also the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-swift-package.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s say you will use the some beta version, here 1.3.0-beta.2","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null},{"type":"step","code":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They can be embeded inside your ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"target","type":"text"}]},{"text":" librairies.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}]},{"text":" library provides the main elements like the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The theme contract is defined inside it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrange","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesSosh","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesWireframe","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrangeCompact","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSComponents","type":"text"}]},{"text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensRaw","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensSemantic","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSModules","type":"text"}]},{"text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSFoundations","type":"text"}]},{"text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-libraries.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null}],"contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}]}]},{"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Which of these choices is correct?","type":"text"}]}],"choices":[{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports only SwiftUI.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides UIKit components","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[]},{"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}]}],"choices":[{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product wraps all of them.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[]}]},{"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s suppose we want to define a view for corporate apps with headings, texts, buttons and images."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"How can we do that?"}],"title":"Define information cards","action":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view","overridingTitle":"Get started","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}]}}],"kind":"project","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies"]}],"metadata":{"role":"project","category":"Orange Unified Design System","categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","title":"Swift Package integration"},"references":{"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)":{"url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents-(onboarding)","role":"overview","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","kind":"overview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discovering a new framework can be exciting and scary."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"With this tutorial, you will learn how to embed OUDS Swift Package and define views tailored for your brand."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It has beend esigned for local events and meetups."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Let’s play!"}],"title":"Swift Package Onboarding Tutorial","type":"topic"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-onboarding-4-going-further":{"url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-onboarding-4-going-further","estimatedTime":"10min","role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-4-going-further","kind":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Since you have learned how OUDS works with theme, themeable view, components, tuning and view modifiers, it is time now to discover some online resources."}],"type":"topic","title":"Going further with more resources"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-onboarding-3-components-showcase#Merge-components-in-a-richer-view":{"role":"pseudoSymbol","type":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContrac